sources.data_found: NCES College Navigator 2023-2024 Data: Lists Bachelor's degrees awarded in Computer and Information Sciences (Category 11) as 20.

student_data.notes: St. John Fisher University is primarily a teaching institution. Student counts are estimated based on degree production reported to NCES (IPEDS). In the most recent reporting year, 20 degrees were awarded in Computer Information Sciences. Assuming a 4-year steady state (20 * 4), the estimated undergraduate CS enrollment is approx 80 students. The university does not offer a dedicated M.S. or Ph.D. in Computer Science.

gpu_resources.notes: St. John Fisher University is a smaller private university without a dedicated Research Computing/HPC center. Extensive searches for 'HPC', 'Cluster', 'Supercomputer', and 'GPU nodes' on the university domain yielded 0 results. CS instruction relies on standard computer labs and personal devices. No server-grade GPU resources (H100/A100) are publicly documented as owned by the institution. [WARNING: Original source was inaccessible, using fallback.]

compute_credits.description: No public data found regarding cloud compute credits.

analysis_notes: The university (formerly St. John Fisher College) focuses on undergraduate liberal arts and professional programs (Nursing, Business, Pharmacy). It does not maintain the infrastructure for high-performance computing found at R1 research universities. All GPU resource counts are set to 0 based on the lack of any research computing division or infrastructure documentation.
